sql:
SELECT p.publication_id, p.title, p.type, p.publisher_id, pub.publisher_name
FROM publications AS p
JOIN publishers AS pub ON p.publisher_id = pub.publisher_id;

SELECT author_name
FROM authors
WHERE affiliation = 'Department of Computer Science, University of Example';

SELECT COUNT(*) as access_count
FROM access_logs
WHERE publication_id = 1;

SELECT *
FROM publications
WHERE publisher_id = 1;

SELECT a.author_name
FROM authors a
INNER JOIN publishers p ON a.author_name = p.publisher_name;

external_knowledge:
In this context, comprehensive information about publications includes the publication ID, title, type, ranking, publisher ID, h-index, impact score, publication date, volume, issue, pages, DOI, citation count, and abstract; 
Aggregated authors' details include the total number of authors, names, emails, departments, positions, research interests, and ORCIDs; 
Access logs include the total number of accesses and the number of downloads for each publication.
